description:
Physics simulation configuration using real-world units.

COORDINATE SYSTEM (Real-World Physics):
- Origin (0, 0) is at BOTTOM-LEFT corner of the simulation canvas
- X increases to the right
- Y increases UPWARD (like standard physics)
- Positive Y velocity = upward motion

CANVAS:
- The simulation canvas is 800 × 600 pixels.
- SI canvas size is (800 / pixelsPerUnit) × (600 / pixelsPerUnit) in the configured unit.
- With pixelsPerUnit=10 and unit="m" → 80m × 60m canvas.
- Pick pixelsPerUnit so the LARGEST object is roughly 10–25% of the smaller (600 px) dimension.

OBJECTS:
- Each object is described by its center (x, y), bounding-box width and height, and an svg name from the public manifest.
- The svg name drives BOTH the visual sprite AND the collider shape (rectangle / circle / convex hull). The collider is scaled to fit within width × height.
- Width and height should reflect the typical real-world bounding box of the named object (e.g., a soccer_ball is ~0.22 m, a brick_block is ~0.5 m, a person is ~1.8 m tall).
- Always pass the same configured unit; do not mix.

GUIDELINES:
- Keep simulations simple: 1-3 objects, focus on 1-2 physics concepts
- Always include at least one control for interactivity
- Use outputs to show current state, graphs to show history
- Use clear, educational labels
- All values (positions, velocities, sizes) are in the configured unit

EXAMPLE 1 - Vertical Ball Toss:
{
  "title": "Toss Ball",
  "description": "Toss a ball vertically and observe acceleration versus velocity",
  "environment": {
    "walls": [],
    "gravity": 9.8,
    "unit": "m",
    "pixelsPerUnit": 10,
    "physicsEngine": "rapier"
  },
  "objects": [
    {
      "id": "ball",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 10,
      "width": 6,
      "height": 6,
      "svg": "baseball",
      "velocity": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20
      },
      "restitution": 0.8,
      "frictionAir": 0
    }
  ],
  "controls": [
    {
      "type": "slider",
      "label": "Initial Velocity",
      "targetObj": "ball",
      "property": "velocity.y",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 30,
      "step": 0.01,
      "defaultValue": 20
    }
  ],
  "outputs": [
    {
      "title": "Ball Outputs",
      "values": [
        {
          "label": "Velocity",
          "targetObj": "ball",
          "property": "velocity.y",
          "unit": "m/s"
        },
        {
          "label": "Acceleration",
          "targetObj": "ball",
          "property": "acceleration.y",
          "unit": "m/s²"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "graphs": [
    {
      "type": "line",
      "title": "Velocity and Acceleration Over Time",
      "yAxisRange": {
        "min": -30,
        "max": 30
      },
      "yAxisLabel": "Value (m/s, m/s²)",
      "lines": [
        {
          "label": "Velocity",
          "targetObj": "ball",
          "property": "velocity.y",
          "color": "#ff6bff"
        },
        {
          "label": "Acceleration",
          "targetObj": "ball",
          "property": "acceleration.y",
          "color": "#4ecdc4"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

EXAMPLE 2 - Two Boxes Collision:
{
  "title": "Two Boxes Collision",
  "description": "Adjust the velocities to see the boxes move and collide",
  "environment": {
    "walls": [
      "left",
      "right",
      "bottom"
    ],
    "gravity": 9.8,
    "unit": "m",
    "pixelsPerUnit": 10,
    "physicsEngine": "rapier"
  },
  "objects": [
    {
      "id": "boxA",
      "x": 15,
      "y": 50,
      "width": 6,
      "height": 6,
      "svg": "box",
      "velocity": {
        "x": 5,
        "y": 0
      },
      "restitution": 0.8,
      "frictionAir": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "boxB",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 40,
      "width": 6,
      "height": 6,
      "svg": "box",
      "velocity": {
        "x": -5,
        "y": 0
      },
      "restitution": 0.8,
      "frictionAir": 0
    }
  ],
  "controls": [
    {
      "type": "slider",
      "label": "Box A Velocity",
      "targetObj": "boxA",
      "property": "velocity.x",
      "min": -30,
      "max": 30,
      "step": 0.1,
      "defaultValue": 5
    },
    {
      "type": "slider",
      "label": "Box B Velocity",
      "targetObj": "boxB",
      "property": "velocity.x",
      "min": -30,
      "max": 30,
      "step": 0.1,
      "defaultValue": -5
    }
  ],
  "outputs": [
    {
      "title": "Box A Outputs",
      "values": [
        {
          "label": "Velocity X",
          "targetObj": "boxA",
          "property": "velocity.x",
          "unit": "m/s"
        },
        {
          "label": "Velocity Y",
          "targetObj": "boxA",
          "property": "velocity.y",
          "unit": "m/s"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Box B Outputs",
      "values": [
        {
          "label": "Velocity X",
          "targetObj": "boxB",
          "property": "velocity.x",
          "unit": "m/s"
        },
        {
          "label": "Velocity Y",
          "targetObj": "boxB",
          "property": "velocity.y",
          "unit": "m/s"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "graphs": [
    {
      "type": "line",
      "title": "Horizontal Velocity Over Time",
      "yAxisRange": {
        "min": -1,
        "max": 1
      },
      "yAxisLabel": "Velocity (m/s)",
      "lines": [
        {
          "label": "Box A Velocity X",
          "targetObj": "boxA",
          "property": "velocity.x",
          "color": "#ff6bff"
        },
        {
          "label": "Box B Velocity X",
          "targetObj": "boxB",
          "property": "velocity.x",
          "color": "#4ecdc4"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line",
      "title": "Horizontal Position Over Time",
      "yAxisRange": {
        "min": -1,
        "max": 1
      },
      "yAxisLabel": "Position (m)",
      "lines": [
        {
          "label": "Box A Position X",
          "targetObj": "boxA",
          "property": "position.x",
          "color": "#ff6bff"
        },
        {
          "label": "Box B Position X",
          "targetObj": "boxB",
          "property": "position.x",
          "color": "#4ecdc4"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
